tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows elevated creatinine, significant proteinuria, glycosuria, and ketonuria, with low urine specific gravity and brown, cloudy urine. These findings suggest impaired renal function, possible nephrotic syndrome or diabetic ketoacidosis, though HbA1c is unexpectedly low. No evidence of urinary tract infection. Further clinical correlation and nephrology evaluation are recommended.
